## PROJECT REPORT
# MODULE-1
For this task, I used an online design tool to create my infographic on digital literacy. The tool helped me organize
information visually using icons, colors, and structured sections. It was easy to use and allowed me to present the 
content in a clean and attractive format.

My design focuses on key aspects of digital literacy, 
including its definition, useful digital tools for students, safe internet practices, professional online presence, 
and email etiquette. Each section highlights important points in a concise manner so that the viewer can quickly understand 
the concepts. I used simple headings and bullet points to make the infographic clear and easy to read.

One thing I found interesting while making this infographic was how visual representation makes information more 
engaging compared to plain text. However, I also found it slightly challenging to fit all the important points into
limited space without making the design look crowded. Overall, this task helped me improve both my understanding of digital 
literacy and my ability to present information creatively.

## MODULE-2
For this task, I chose platforms such as LinkedIn, GitHub, and Google Drive as essential tools for my academic and 
professional growth. Each of these platforms serves a different but important purpose.

LinkedIn is mainly used for building a professional network, showcasing achievements, and applying for internships or
job opportunities. GitHub is useful for storing, managing, and sharing coding projects, which is especially important for 
demonstrating technical skills. Google Drive helps in storing academic files, notes, and projects securely, while also 
allowing easy access and collaboration.

Over the next four years, I plan to actively use LinkedIn to build a strong professional profile and connect with 
industry professionals. I will regularly upload and update my projects on GitHub to create a solid portfolio. Additionally,
I will use Google Drive to organize my study materials and collaborate on group assignments. These platforms will help me 
stay organized, improve my skills, and prepare effectively for future career opportunities

## MODULE-3
For this task, I used HackerRank for coding practice and Google Forms along with Google Sheets for collaboration. On
HackerRank, I created an account and completed a beginner-level problem, which helped me understand basic problem-solving
and coding logic. It also gave me exposure to how coding platforms evaluate solutions.

For the collaboration part, I created a “Digital Literacy Awareness Quiz” using Google Forms with both multiple-choice 
and short-answer questions. The responses were automatically collected and organized in Google Sheets, making it easy to
analyze the data.

These tools will help me academically in multiple ways. HackerRank will improve my coding skills and prepare me for 
technical interviews and placements. Google Forms and Sheets will help me in conducting surveys, collecting data for
projects, and collaborating efficiently with classmates. Overall, these platforms enhance both my technical and 
organizational skills, which are essential for academic success and future career growth.

## MODULE-4
Poor digital communication can often lead to misunderstandings and missed opportunities. For example, a student once 
sent an email to a professor requesting an extension but used an informal tone, did not include a proper subject line, 
and failed to clearly explain the reason. As a result, the professor misunderstood the request and did not respond on time,
which led to a late submission penalty.

This situation could have been handled better by following proper email etiquette. The student should have used a clear 
subject line, a respectful greeting, and a well-structured message explaining the situation briefly and politely. Including 
all necessary details and maintaining a professional tone would have increased the chances of a positive response.

This highlights how effective and professional communication plays a crucial role in academic and professional
environments.

## MODULE-5
While researching cybercrime, I was most surprised by how easily people fall victim to online scams, especially UPI and 
phishing frauds. Many attacks do not require advanced hacking skills; instead, they rely on tricking users into sharing 
sensitive information like OTPs or approving fake payment requests. It was also interesting to learn how quickly such
frauds can happen and how difficult it can be to recover lost money if action is not taken immediately.

As a result of this research, one habit I will personally change is being more cautious while making online transactions.
I will always verify UPI IDs and avoid clicking on unknown links or messages. I will also make sure to never share 
confidential details like OTPs or passwords with anyone. This awareness will help me stay safer online and guide others 
as well.
